title.narrative: OCHA Field activities, Asia and the Pacific (regional)
OCHA Field activities, Asia and the Pacific (regional)

description.narrative: OCHA is the part of the United Nations secretariat responsible for bringing together humanitarian actors to ensure a coherent response to emergencies. It plays a key role in coordinating international humanitarian preparedness and response in the region. OCHA’s work in Asia and the Pacific is focused around four key areas:• Mobilize and coordinate effective and principled humanitarian response in partnership with national and international actors in order to alleviate human suffering in disasters and emergencies.• Advocate the rights of people in need.• Promote preparedness and prevention.• Conduct humanitarian analysis and facilitate sustainable solutions
